### Enrichment
Original Chicago Pizza and Oven Grinder Co is in Lincoln Park, Chicago. Pizza pot pie is made upside-down — cheese first in greased ramekin, then toppings, then dough draped over top. Flip after baking so cheese is on top. Uses store-bought or homemade dough. Cook at 450F about 20 minutes. One of the most sought-after copycat recipes. Ready in 20 minutes with store-bought ingredients.

